title: gesserit's favourites: First Issues for June 2015
description:
Cover:     <a href=" http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/etlJUfEYVG.png" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/etlJUfEYVG.png</a>




Contains:   Broken World    01    (of 04) (2015) (Digital)               (Empire)

            Heart in a Box  01-07 (of 07) (2015) (Digital) (Son of Ultron-Empire)

            Heathen        001            (2015) (Digital)  (TheArchivist-Empire)

            Starve         001            (2015) (Digital)               (Empire)

            The Fiction     01    (of 04) (2015) (Digital)          (Zone-Empire)


            Unprecedently, this instalment actually contains a finished series, and
            not just debut issues. And I didn't even have to cheat: 7-week limited
            run, which means there were 6 weeks between the first and last issue;
            issue 1 was posted a week late, so there were only 5 weeks between first
            and last release; and all of those 5 Weeklies fell into the June window.
            Nice, huh? :D If I count each of those 7 issues separately, obviously
            that publisher (Dark Horse) comes out on top this time - but even
            without that, Image uncharacteristically takes a back seat with only one
            title, behind Boom with two and on par with one independently-published
            book. Anyway, what matters is that it's all good stuff, right? ;)
